WEBVTT

1
00:00:27.831 --> 00:00:29.367
Hi, leave a detailed message

2
00:00:29.433 --> 00:00:32.135
and I'll get back to you
as soon as I possibly can.


3
00:00:32.202 --> 00:00:34.104
Have a great day.

4
00:00:34.171 --> 00:00:36.006
James, this is Steven.

5
00:00:36.073 --> 00:00:38.876
Could you please call
me as soon as possible?


6
00:00:38.942 --> 00:00:39.942
Thanks.

7
00:01:06.103 --> 00:01:07.805
She's asking for you.

8
00:01:10.641 --> 00:01:12.710
She's asking for you.

9
00:01:50.147 --> 00:01:55.486
That's alright, we're
home and we're together.


10
00:01:55.553 --> 00:01:56.587
I'm happy.

11
00:02:00.658 --> 00:02:05.362
I left her a message,
maybe she'll call.


12
00:02:05.429 --> 00:02:07.531
She never has before.

13
00:02:12.402 --> 00:02:14.738
Her Bible, I need her Bible.

14
00:02:32.122 --> 00:02:34.124
Open it to the bookmark.

15
00:02:40.798 --> 00:02:42.966
Take her Bible, Steven.

16
00:02:44.334 --> 00:02:47.571
Forgive her, and ask
her to forgive us.


17
00:02:51.775 --> 00:02:55.579
We loved her, Steven,
but we failed her.


18
00:02:57.180 --> 00:03:01.051
Promise me you will
give her the Bible.


19
00:03:01.118 --> 00:03:02.219
Forgive her.

20
00:03:03.787 --> 00:03:05.656
Ask her forgiveness.

21
00:03:12.129 --> 00:03:13.130
I promise.

22
00:03:14.498 --> 00:03:16.634
Thank you, Steven.

23
00:03:17.501 --> 00:03:20.571
Please remember that I love you.

24
00:03:22.172 --> 00:03:25.208
I'll be waiting
for you in heaven.


25
00:03:51.401 --> 00:03:53.136
She's with God now.

26
00:03:58.542 --> 00:04:00.944
You did the right thing,

27
00:04:02.512 --> 00:04:04.214
bringing her home.

28
00:05:23.260 --> 00:05:24.260
It's James.

29
00:05:25.729 --> 00:05:27.731
You've called at
a bad time, James.


30
00:05:27.798 --> 00:05:29.933
I'm sorry I
didn't call sooner.


31
00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:31.702
Miranda and I have
been very, very busy.


32
00:05:31.769 --> 00:05:33.336
Abigail is gone.

33
00:05:34.672 --> 00:05:36.239
I was hoping Miranda
would come back


34
00:05:36.306 --> 00:05:40.410
to see her before
it was too late.


35
00:05:40.477 --> 00:05:41.979
Now it's too late.

36
00:05:43.847 --> 00:05:45.783
The funeral was this morning.

37
00:05:45.849 --> 00:05:48.451
I'm so sorry, is
there anything I can do?


38
00:05:48.518 --> 00:05:49.753
Nothing.

39
00:05:51.421 --> 00:05:52.956
I'll tell Miranda,

40
00:05:53.023 --> 00:05:54.692
I think it's something
she ought to know.


41
00:05:54.758 --> 00:05:57.294
Don't you tell her a thing.

42
00:05:58.662 --> 00:06:01.398
Abigail had me promise
to do one thing,


43
00:06:01.464 --> 00:06:03.366
and I'm going to do it.

44
00:06:06.536 --> 00:06:09.506
That's my business, James.

45
00:06:09.572 --> 00:06:11.308
Look, I wanted you to know

46
00:06:11.374 --> 00:06:13.944
because you were a
comfort to Abigail,


47
00:06:14.011 --> 00:06:17.447
letting us know how
Miranda was doing.


48
00:06:17.514 --> 00:06:21.885
But Abigail is gone now and I
have her wishes to consider.


49
00:06:23.954 --> 00:06:27.590
I will tell Miranda
that Abigail is gone,


50
00:06:27.657 --> 00:06:28.926
to her face.

51
00:06:28.992 --> 00:06:30.352
I don't think
that's a good idea.


52
00:06:30.393 --> 00:06:35.198
It's a terrible
idea, but I promised.


53
00:06:35.265 --> 00:06:36.934
I need your address.

54
00:06:37.868 --> 00:06:39.436
I don't know, Steven.

55
00:06:39.502 --> 00:06:41.538
Listen, I've got to go.

56
00:08:05.823 --> 00:08:07.958
Forgiveness.

57
00:08:41.491 --> 00:08:44.828
It's just not the
same without her.


58
00:11:09.339 --> 00:11:12.775
I will tell Miranda
that Abigail is gone,


59
00:11:12.842 --> 00:11:14.044
to her face.

60
00:11:16.446 --> 00:11:20.450
Lord, am I doing
the right thing?


61
00:11:20.517 --> 00:11:24.054
I don't know if I can
keep this to myself.


62
00:13:16.233 --> 00:13:18.067
I'm headed to the office.

63
00:13:18.135 --> 00:13:19.169
Okay.

64
00:13:20.670 --> 00:13:23.240
You look good.
Thank you.


65
00:13:26.709 --> 00:13:29.179
Let's not talk about
dinner right now, okay?


66
00:13:29.246 --> 00:13:32.915
There's something I really
need to talk to you about.


67
00:13:36.186 --> 00:13:38.655
Sit down, please.

68
00:13:43.193 --> 00:13:45.061
You're starting to worry me.

69
00:13:45.128 --> 00:13:47.664
Please don't be mad at me.

70
00:13:49.332 --> 00:13:52.602
I've been speaking with
Steven for a few months now.


71
00:13:55.172 --> 00:13:56.715
You know I want nothing
to do with them,


72
00:13:56.739 --> 00:13:59.776
and you've been talking to
him for months behind my back?


73
00:13:59.842 --> 00:14:02.011
I wanted to let them
know that you were alright,


74
00:14:02.078 --> 00:14:05.348
but that's not the
issue right now.


75
00:14:09.051 --> 00:14:11.087
He called me a few months ago.

76
00:14:11.154 --> 00:14:13.122
Abigail was sick.

77
00:14:13.190 --> 00:14:14.891
Cancer, I'm sorry.

78
00:14:21.731 --> 00:14:24.701
She passed away
a few days ago.


79
00:14:32.442 --> 00:14:37.079
Well there's nothing
I can do about that now.


80
00:14:37.146 --> 00:14:38.915
When's the funeral?

81
00:14:40.217 --> 00:14:42.652
It was earlier this week.

82
00:14:46.289 --> 00:14:49.125
Well I wouldn't
have gone anyway.


83
00:14:49.192 --> 00:14:50.192
Wait.

84
00:14:52.495 --> 00:14:54.664
You talk to them for
months behind my back,


85
00:14:54.731 --> 00:14:58.134
and you pick now, after
Abigail's gone, to tell me that?


86
00:14:58.201 --> 00:14:59.445
I didn't know what else to do.

87
00:14:59.469 --> 00:15:02.572
James, they lied
to me for years.


88
00:15:02.639 --> 00:15:04.207
I was going to
church every Sunday,


89
00:15:04.274 --> 00:15:05.584
and everybody else knew
they were lying to me.


90
00:15:05.608 --> 00:15:08.245
And now you're lying to me?

91
00:15:11.147 --> 00:15:12.782
That went well.

92
00:15:42.078 --> 00:15:43.078
Liars.

93
00:15:48.150 --> 00:15:49.786
And now he's a liar.

94
00:15:51.020 --> 00:15:55.057
Knock knock,
Miranda, are you back there?


95
00:15:55.124 --> 00:15:56.693
Yeah, come on in.

96
00:16:04.967 --> 00:16:06.269
Thank you.

97
00:16:06.336 --> 00:16:10.407
I just had to get out of
that house for a minute.


98
00:16:12.575 --> 00:16:14.076
Oh, I'm interrupting you.

99
00:16:14.143 --> 00:16:16.913
No, no, no, it's fine.

100
00:16:16.979 --> 00:16:19.849
Turns out I needed some company.

101
00:16:19.916 --> 00:16:21.183
Me too.

102
00:16:21.250 --> 00:16:22.761
Who would think with
doctors and nurses


103
00:16:22.785 --> 00:16:24.597
and therapists barging
around the house all day


104
00:16:24.621 --> 00:16:26.823
I'd need company, but...

105
00:16:28.057 --> 00:16:31.193
I could use a moment of
quiet time with a friend.


106
00:16:33.463 --> 00:16:36.299
He's getting better every day.

107
00:16:36.366 --> 00:16:39.836
He recognizes me now and
the therapist said that


108
00:16:39.902 --> 00:16:42.872
he should be out of the
wheelchair in a couple of months.


109
00:16:42.939 --> 00:16:47.109
And the nurses are optimistic
too, but the doctors...


110
00:16:47.176 --> 00:16:49.145
Don't listen to the doctors.

111
00:16:49.211 --> 00:16:50.411
Doctors are always pessimists,

112
00:16:50.447 --> 00:16:52.649
listen to the therapists
and the nurses.


113
00:16:52.715 --> 00:16:55.284
They're the ones spending
all this time with Michael.


114
00:16:55.352 --> 00:16:59.255
Yeah, they spend more
time with him than I do.


115
00:16:59.322 --> 00:17:02.559
And with that realization,
I need to get home.


116
00:17:02.625 --> 00:17:05.027
Mike will be
wondering where I am.


117
00:17:05.094 --> 00:17:07.964
Well, come back any
time, I'll make some tea.


118
00:17:08.030 --> 00:17:11.167
I took our health and the
lives we had for granted.


119
00:17:11.233 --> 00:17:12.435
Never again.

120
00:18:22.104 --> 00:18:26.676
Why am I doing this to myself?

121
00:18:28.411 --> 00:18:31.548
Hmm, car's running
a little rough.


122
00:18:31.614 --> 00:18:35.685
I think I'll get off
the interstate for now.


123
00:19:01.778 --> 00:19:03.446
You were working
late last night.


124
00:19:03.513 --> 00:19:05.448
I tried not to wake you.

125
00:19:05.515 --> 00:19:07.784
Yeah, I didn't sleep well.

126
00:19:07.850 --> 00:19:10.953
Listen, I'm sorry I went
against your wishes.


127
00:19:11.020 --> 00:19:13.956
I haven't spoken to
them for years, by choice.


128
00:19:14.023 --> 00:19:16.092
You had no right
to just call them.


129
00:19:16.158 --> 00:19:17.158
I know.

130
00:19:18.127 --> 00:19:19.638
And Abigail dying
doesn't change that.


131
00:19:19.662 --> 00:19:22.632
I'm not going back there, ever.

132
00:19:24.033 --> 00:19:27.069
I have a birth mother,
we have a relationship.


133
00:19:27.136 --> 00:19:28.136
That's it.

134
00:19:31.541 --> 00:19:35.678
I better do something
before he gets here.


135
00:20:37.339 --> 00:20:39.141
I'm pretty good with cars.

136
00:20:39.208 --> 00:20:41.143
That makes one of us.

137
00:20:43.479 --> 00:20:44.180
Steven.

138
00:20:44.246 --> 00:20:45.081
Joseph.

139
00:20:45.147 --> 00:20:46.749
Nice to meet you.

140
00:20:48.217 --> 00:20:51.053
Guess I'll have to
walk back into town.


141
00:20:51.120 --> 00:20:53.590
Gotta be a couple miles.

142
00:20:53.656 --> 00:20:56.392
I just walked
through that town.


143
00:20:56.458 --> 00:20:58.460
It's nice, but I'm don't think

144
00:20:58.527 --> 00:21:01.097
there's a mechanic
there that can help you.


145
00:21:01.163 --> 00:21:03.299
Not on a Saturday, anyway.

146
00:21:04.567 --> 00:21:06.869
Is it Saturday already?

147
00:21:06.936 --> 00:21:12.208
When you're retired the days
just sorta run together.


148
00:21:12.274 --> 00:21:15.377
Every day is a gift
from the Lord, Steven.


149
00:21:15.444 --> 00:21:19.816
Trouble is, some people think
he gave us an endless supply.


150
00:21:22.518 --> 00:21:25.788
I think I feel a
loose wire here.


151
00:21:25.855 --> 00:21:27.924
That might've gotten it.

152
00:21:29.025 --> 00:21:31.961
Alright, hop in
and start 'er up.


153
00:21:53.282 --> 00:21:54.350
You're all set to go.

154
00:21:56.485 --> 00:21:58.287
Los Angeles.

155
00:22:01.190 --> 00:22:01.891
That'd be great.

156
00:22:01.958 --> 00:22:03.826
Wonderful, hop in.

157
00:22:05.662 --> 00:22:07.797
You've reached my
cell phone voicemail,


158
00:22:07.864 --> 00:22:10.566
please leave a message.

159
00:22:10.633 --> 00:22:12.902
I assume you're
already headed this way.


160
00:22:12.969 --> 00:22:17.306
Our address is 407 Valley
View Drive, Sherman Oaks.


161
00:22:22.111 --> 00:22:24.981
In for a penny, in for a pound.

162
00:22:25.047 --> 00:22:27.249
I hope Miranda can
forgive me for this,


163
00:22:27.316 --> 00:22:29.752
I'm keeping this from her too.

164
00:22:35.191 --> 00:22:38.160
Sure is nice to finally get
away from all that grey sky,


165
00:22:38.227 --> 00:22:40.229
but it's getting colder.

166
00:22:42.665 --> 00:22:44.734
By the way, I have
an extra jacket.


167
00:22:44.801 --> 00:22:47.704
You can borrow it if you want.

168
00:22:51.573 --> 00:22:55.111
Not exactly the
talkative type, are you?


169
00:22:56.879 --> 00:22:59.348
I'm just enjoying the scenery.

170
00:22:59.415 --> 00:23:03.019
It's a lot to take in
traveling this fast.


171
00:23:03.085 --> 00:23:08.324
You're the first
person who's said I drive fast.


172
00:23:08.390 --> 00:23:11.293
Well, I've been walking.

173
00:23:11.360 --> 00:23:14.096
I like driving
these old highways.


174
00:23:14.163 --> 00:23:18.267
You get to see a little bit of
what America used to be like.


175
00:23:18.334 --> 00:23:20.536
You miss a lot driving
the interstates,


176
00:23:20.602 --> 00:23:22.872
and even more when you fly.

177
00:23:23.840 --> 00:23:26.843
I like this speed just fine,

178
00:23:28.945 --> 00:23:31.781
and the scenery is beautiful.

179
00:23:33.515 --> 00:23:38.020
The scenery will get
better as we go west.


180
00:23:38.087 --> 00:23:39.822
Ah, yes, the mountains.

181
00:23:39.889 --> 00:23:42.691
I am looking forward to that.

182
00:23:42.759 --> 00:23:45.527
Have you ever been
through the Rockies?


183
00:23:45.594 --> 00:23:46.963
No, not yet.

184
00:23:48.765 --> 00:23:51.500
Well, you're in
for a real treat.


185
00:23:51.567 --> 00:23:53.235
Take your time.

186
00:23:53.302 --> 00:23:58.540
I haven't had my fill of
these wide open spaces.


187
00:23:58.607 --> 00:24:02.845
Me, I get tired
of the flat after a while.


188
00:24:04.914 --> 00:24:07.750
I could never tire of this.

189
00:24:09.085 --> 00:24:10.486
Maybe you're right.

190
00:24:10.552 --> 00:24:14.423
It does have a sort of
stark beauty about it.


191
00:24:41.517 --> 00:24:43.452
What'd you get?

192
00:24:43.519 --> 00:24:45.888
Bread and peanut butter.

193
00:24:56.565 --> 00:25:00.970
Yeah, peanut butter,
the world's perfect food.


194
00:25:16.485 --> 00:25:18.020
Good sandwich.

195
00:25:47.416 --> 00:25:51.988
We've gotta stop for the
night, I'm getting too tired.


196
00:25:53.856 --> 00:25:56.192
We're in Pueblo, Colorado.

197
00:25:57.026 --> 00:25:59.228
I'm gonna get a room.

198
00:25:59.295 --> 00:26:02.731
I'm too old to
bunk with somebody.


199
00:26:02.798 --> 00:26:04.400
That's fine.

200
00:26:04.466 --> 00:26:07.870
No reason for me to
spend money on a room.


201
00:26:07.937 --> 00:26:12.774
I don't mind sleeping
outside, I like the view.


202
00:26:12.841 --> 00:26:14.376
Suit yourself.

203
00:26:37.766 --> 00:26:38.700
See you in the morning.

204
00:26:38.767 --> 00:26:39.902
Alright.

205
00:27:32.955 --> 00:27:35.057
Hey, Joseph!

206
00:27:37.026 --> 00:27:38.927
Did you decide the
room was too stuffy?


207
00:27:38.995 --> 00:27:40.372
I decided that
spending the extra money


208
00:27:40.396 --> 00:27:43.232
for another room
wasn't a bad idea.


209
00:27:43.299 --> 00:27:45.801
Besides that, it's gonna
rain, you'll get drenched.


210
00:27:48.070 --> 00:27:49.638
I guess you're right.

211
00:27:49.705 --> 00:27:54.076
You got the car running,
it's the least I can do.


212
00:27:54.143 --> 00:27:55.511
Okay, come on.

213
00:28:05.787 --> 00:28:10.226
Thank you Lord for
providing me a friend


214
00:28:10.292 --> 00:28:13.029
that cared enough
to give me shelter.


215
00:29:11.653 --> 00:29:14.022
I found some tea bags
next to the coffee maker.


216
00:29:14.090 --> 00:29:15.900
Would you care to join
me in a cup of green tea?


217
00:29:15.924 --> 00:29:17.193
Come on in.

218
00:29:18.094 --> 00:29:19.361
It'll help you sleep.

219
00:29:19.428 --> 00:29:21.073
I don't normally need
help getting to sleep,


220
00:29:21.097 --> 00:29:23.799
but a cup of tea sounds nice.

221
00:29:26.768 --> 00:29:28.337
I don't mean to bother you.

222
00:29:28.404 --> 00:29:30.139
I just enjoy sipping
a cup of green tea


223
00:29:30.206 --> 00:29:33.609
and having intelligent
conversation in the evening,


224
00:29:33.675 --> 00:29:36.044
when the opportunity
presents itself.


225
00:29:36.112 --> 00:29:38.080
It's a good idea.

226
00:29:39.615 --> 00:29:40.892
I was just going to
do a little reading


227
00:29:40.916 --> 00:29:42.851
before going to sleep.

228
00:29:42.918 --> 00:29:45.721
That's a fine choice.

229
00:29:45.787 --> 00:29:47.123
What's your favorite book?

230
00:29:47.189 --> 00:29:48.657
Acts.

231
00:29:48.724 --> 00:29:52.594
I like reading about
action, not just words.


232
00:29:54.096 --> 00:29:57.666
I remember that
printing, 1970s, I think.


233
00:30:00.136 --> 00:30:02.238
You've got a great memory.

234
00:30:02.304 --> 00:30:05.207
It was a gift to my daughter.

235
00:30:11.713 --> 00:30:15.384
That's a long story
and very private.


236
00:30:18.086 --> 00:30:20.122
I don't mean to pry.

237
00:30:23.792 --> 00:30:24.993
Nice tea by the way.

238
00:30:25.060 --> 00:30:26.428
It was a good idea,

239
00:30:26.495 --> 00:30:31.933
but we've got all day for
intelligent conversation.


240
00:30:32.000 --> 00:30:35.070
I can tell you're busy.

241
00:30:35.137 --> 00:30:37.739
I can finish this in my room.

242
00:30:41.543 --> 00:30:44.079
What time are we checking out?

243
00:30:44.146 --> 00:30:47.383
I'd like to get on the
road by eight o'clock.


244
00:30:47.449 --> 00:30:50.085
Again, thank you for the room.

245
00:30:50.152 --> 00:30:51.787
It was very nice.

246
00:30:51.853 --> 00:30:53.755
You're welcome.

247
00:30:53.822 --> 00:30:54.822
Good night.

248
00:31:08.204 --> 00:31:10.306
Good morning, sleep well?

249
00:31:11.307 --> 00:31:13.375
Sure did.

250
00:31:25.254 --> 00:31:27.356
Just so you know, I
like to stop now and then


251
00:31:27.423 --> 00:31:30.959
and stretch my legs,
and enjoy the scenery.


252
00:32:09.565 --> 00:32:13.034
Boy, I wish Abigail was
here with me to see this.


253
00:32:13.101 --> 00:32:15.471
She would really enjoy it.

254
00:32:20.442 --> 00:32:21.910
Oh, I miss her.

255
00:32:42.664 --> 00:32:46.234
Steven, I'm having
second thoughts about this.


256
00:32:46.302 --> 00:32:48.337
Please give me a call.

257
00:32:49.204 --> 00:32:50.906
I'm already in Colorado.

258
00:32:50.972 --> 00:32:54.410
