And that's what they promote.

507
00:57:30.918 --> 00:57:34.688
A modern day
Sodom and Gomorrah.


508
00:57:34.755 --> 00:57:37.724
Yeah, with a
big electric bill.


509
00:57:37.792 --> 00:57:39.259
That's right.

510
00:57:41.829 --> 00:57:45.099
You can just drop me
off and keep driving.


511
00:57:45.165 --> 00:57:49.203
What is so important
about Las Vegas anyway?


512
00:57:51.171 --> 00:57:53.573
Let's just say I
have some work to do


513
00:57:53.640 --> 00:57:56.143
and leave it at that, alright?

514
00:57:58.612 --> 00:57:59.814
I guess we both have things

515
00:57:59.880 --> 00:58:02.649
we'd rather not talk about.

516
00:58:02.716 --> 00:58:04.184
I suppose so.

517
00:58:05.519 --> 00:58:07.021
Let's go.

518
00:58:41.188 --> 00:58:43.390
The New Testament
tells us that often Jesus


519
00:58:43.457 --> 00:58:48.262
and his apostles spent
time among sinners.


520
00:58:48.328 --> 00:58:50.264
Well, if they were
going to spread his word,


521
00:58:50.330 --> 00:58:53.100
that's where they needed to be.

522
00:58:55.970 --> 00:58:59.806
Which is why I need
to go to Las Vegas.


523
00:59:01.175 --> 00:59:03.911
Is that why you're
hitchhiking across country?


524
00:59:03.978 --> 00:59:05.913
To spread the Word?

525
00:59:09.283 --> 00:59:11.818
I have a light to shine
in the darkness, Steven.


526
00:59:11.886 --> 00:59:15.055
Then, why don't
you let me help you?


527
00:59:18.993 --> 00:59:21.929
You have your
own path to walk.


528
00:59:37.677 --> 00:59:42.249
Kinda puts a bit of perspective
on our problems, doesn't it?


529
01:01:06.633 --> 01:01:08.702
Might as well
hold onto that coat.


530
01:01:08.768 --> 01:01:13.240
I hear it gets cold in Las
Vegas, especially at night.


531
01:01:26.086 --> 01:01:28.755
Are you sure you
want to do this?


532
01:01:28.822 --> 01:01:29.822
I am.

533
01:01:32.092 --> 01:01:35.495
Well, seeing as we'll
be parting company,


534
01:01:35.562 --> 01:01:38.465
there's something else
I want to tell you.


535
01:01:41.768 --> 01:01:46.573
When James called to
tell us Miranda was okay,


536
01:01:46.640 --> 01:01:49.009
Abigail wanted to leave
right there and then,


537
01:01:49.076 --> 01:01:52.246
to go to Los Angeles,
but I refused.


538
01:01:59.219 --> 01:02:01.321
I was being prideful.

539
01:02:02.622 --> 01:02:05.959
I told Abigail if
Amanda wanted to see us,


540
01:02:06.026 --> 01:02:07.694
she knew where we lived.

541
01:02:07.761 --> 01:02:12.699
We weren't going to be
the ones who gave in.


542
01:02:12.766 --> 01:02:17.337
Shortly after that, Abigail
was too sick to travel.


543
01:02:19.706 --> 01:02:24.278
I had denied Abigail a
chance to see Miranda again.


544
01:02:26.280 --> 01:02:29.015
She died shortly after that.

545
01:02:34.454 --> 01:02:38.892
Well at least you're
fulfilling her last wish now.


546
01:02:38.958 --> 01:02:41.661
Abigail would be proud of you.

547
01:02:43.963 --> 01:02:44.963
I do.

548
01:02:46.166 --> 01:02:50.137
And I know one day you'll
be united in heaven.


549
01:03:06.586 --> 01:03:08.988
Thank you for the ride, Steven.

550
01:03:09.055 --> 01:03:10.857
You be careful here now.

551
01:03:10.924 --> 01:03:12.926
Thank you, be careful driving.

552
01:03:12.992 --> 01:03:14.261
Oh, I will.

553
01:03:14.328 --> 01:03:16.663
I guess this is goodbye.

554
01:03:16.730 --> 01:03:20.200
Goodbye for now, I'm
sure we'll meet again.


555
01:03:20.267 --> 01:03:21.668
Perhaps.

556
01:03:21.735 --> 01:03:23.903
Good luck to you.

557
01:03:23.970 --> 01:03:25.038
Thank you.

558
01:04:09.216 --> 01:04:10.584
Boy I'm tired.

559
01:04:10.650 --> 01:04:15.155
I think I'm gonna pull
over and take a little nap.


560
01:04:29.969 --> 01:04:32.639
Not ideal, but it'll have to do.

561
01:05:27.261 --> 01:05:30.464
Let me get that,
it could be work.


562
01:05:50.484 --> 01:05:52.151
Hello, James, it's Steven.

563
01:05:52.218 --> 01:05:54.321
Hello, it's good
to hear from you.


564
01:05:54.388 --> 01:05:55.689
Where are you?

565
01:05:56.956 --> 01:05:59.859
I'm at Baker, I'll be
there in about three hours.


566
01:05:59.926 --> 01:06:01.094
That's just fine.

567
01:06:01.160 --> 01:06:02.171
Do you know how to get here?

568
01:06:02.195 --> 01:06:03.397
I've got a map.

569
01:06:03.463 --> 01:06:06.199
If I have any
trouble, I'll call.


570
01:06:06.266 --> 01:06:08.502
Alright, see you
in a few hours.


571
01:06:08.568 --> 01:06:11.671
James, do you
think she'll see me?


572
01:06:12.872 --> 01:06:15.241
I don't know
if she wants to see you,


573
01:06:15.309 --> 01:06:16.843
but she's not going anywhere.

574
01:06:16.910 --> 01:06:20.113
I suppose that'll
have to be good enough.


575
01:06:20.179 --> 01:06:21.281
See you soon.

576
01:06:21.348 --> 01:06:22.382
Bye.

577
01:06:29.989 --> 01:06:31.190
I spoke to Steven.

578
01:06:31.257 --> 01:06:34.394
He's gonna be here
in a few hours.


579
01:06:35.895 --> 01:06:39.032
Listen, maybe I can make
us all something for lunch.


580
01:06:39.098 --> 01:06:40.300
That'd be great.

581
01:06:40.367 --> 01:06:41.611
Listen, I gotta
go to the office.


582
01:06:41.635 --> 01:06:44.438
I'll be back in a
few hours, okay?


583
01:06:44.504 --> 01:06:45.839
Don't be late.

584
01:06:45.905 --> 01:06:47.006
Okay.

585
01:07:27.113 --> 01:07:28.882
Well, this is nice.

586
01:07:43.397 --> 01:07:44.398
Here I go.

587
01:08:09.423 --> 01:08:12.258
Did you forget your
keys again, James?


588
01:08:12.325 --> 01:08:13.493
Hi, Pumpkin.

589
01:08:22.368 --> 01:08:23.603
Hi, Dad.

590
01:08:26.372 --> 01:08:27.373
You wanna come in?

591
01:08:27.441 --> 01:08:29.576
I made some iced tea.

592
01:08:30.376 --> 01:08:31.376
I'd love that.

593
01:09:03.176 --> 01:09:04.611
You look great.

594
01:09:06.480 --> 01:09:07.681
Thanks.

595
01:09:10.550 --> 01:09:13.587
I guess we have a
lot to talk about.


596
01:09:13.653 --> 01:09:18.024
I didn't come here to talk
about the last 25 years.


597
01:09:24.564 --> 01:09:26.633
To bring you this.

598
01:09:36.442 --> 01:09:39.579
It's my Bible
from Sunday School.


599
01:09:42.015 --> 01:09:46.720
Before she died, your
mother wanted me to bring this


600
01:09:46.786 --> 01:09:49.689
and to ask for your forgiveness.

601
01:09:57.797 --> 01:09:59.766
We made a mistake.

602
01:10:02.702 --> 01:10:05.338
Your mother wanted
you to know that,


603
01:10:05.404 --> 01:10:07.741
and to bring you that Bible.

604
01:10:10.677 --> 01:10:15.014
All of this time I've been
so angry at the both of you,


605
01:10:18.618 --> 01:10:20.286
and I'm just
beginning to realize


606
01:10:20.353 --> 01:10:23.022
I had nothing to be angry about.

607
01:10:24.423 --> 01:10:26.125
And now she's gone

608
01:10:30.263 --> 01:10:33.867
and I didn't get the chance
to tell her that I was wrong,


609
01:10:33.933 --> 01:10:36.670
and ask for her forgiveness.

610
01:10:38.972 --> 01:10:43.242
She forgives you, and
one day you'll know that,


611
01:10:44.778 --> 01:10:47.614
because God forgives you too.

612
01:10:50.717 --> 01:10:54.153
I don't pray, I
don't go to church.


613
01:10:54.220 --> 01:10:57.657
Don't you think
it's time to start?


614
01:11:10.336 --> 01:11:16.375
I forgive you Dad,
do you forgive me?


615
01:11:16.442 --> 01:11:21.014
I just drove over 2,000 miles
to tell this to your face.


616
01:11:22.816 --> 01:11:23.883
I forgive you.

617
01:11:37.631 --> 01:11:39.833
Now tell me about James.

618
01:11:58.217 --> 01:12:02.789
Lord, please
help me make a difference.


619
01:12:07.961 --> 01:12:09.796
- Hi, Hon.
- Hey.


620
01:12:10.697 --> 01:12:13.199
This is my husband.

621
01:12:13.266 --> 01:12:14.634
You must be James.

622
01:12:14.701 --> 01:12:17.003
Honey, this is my
father, Steven Campbell.


623
01:12:17.070 --> 01:12:18.180
It's nice to
finally meet you, sir.


624
01:12:18.204 --> 01:12:19.505
You too.

625
01:12:19.572 --> 01:12:21.132
And thanks for helping
make this happen.


626
01:12:21.174 --> 01:12:22.441
You got it.

627
01:12:22.508 --> 01:12:25.144
You were supposed
to be home sooner.


628
01:12:25.211 --> 01:12:26.980
I know, I saw you two
talking on the porch


629
01:12:27.046 --> 01:12:30.717
and I figured to give
you a little time alone.


630
01:12:30.784 --> 01:12:33.052
Thank you, we needed it.

631
01:12:33.119 --> 01:12:34.654
Oh, we did.

632
01:12:34.721 --> 01:12:36.622
I'm going to take
my Bible inside.


633
01:12:36.690 --> 01:12:38.624
Would you like something
to drink, some iced tea?


634
01:12:38.692 --> 01:12:39.859
Yes, please.

635
01:12:40.626 --> 01:12:42.328
What a sweetheart.

636
01:12:44.263 --> 01:12:47.466
It looks like you guys had
a pretty good conversation.


637
01:12:47.533 --> 01:12:50.436
It took a while, but
we found a good place.


638
01:12:50.503 --> 01:12:52.171
And it's all thanks to you.

639
01:12:52.238 --> 01:12:54.507
Well, I just couldn't
see her carrying around


640
01:12:54.573 --> 01:12:56.242
all that anger and pity.

641
01:12:56.309 --> 01:13:00.646
It was really affecting her,
spiritually, emotionally.


642
01:13:00.714 --> 01:13:02.148
She told me she would take

643
01:13:02.215 --> 01:13:05.418
her Bible with her
to church on Sunday.


644
01:13:05.484 --> 01:13:07.653
That makes me very happy.

645
01:13:07.721 --> 01:13:09.989
- There you go.
- Thank you.


646
01:13:10.056 --> 01:13:13.559
So, if you don't have
any plans for this evening,


647
01:13:13.626 --> 01:13:15.161
then how about I cook us dinner?

648
01:13:15.228 --> 01:13:18.297
And of course you're
staying with us.


649
01:13:18.364 --> 01:13:19.598
I appreciate the offer,

650
01:13:19.665 --> 01:13:22.668
but I've already
checked into a hotel


651
01:13:22.736 --> 01:13:24.437
and I have plans for later.

652
01:13:26.740 --> 01:13:28.842
Abigail and I always
wanted to watch the sunset


653
01:13:28.908 --> 01:13:33.412
over the Pacific Ocean, but
never had a chance to do that.


654
01:13:33.479 --> 01:13:35.414
I'm gonna do that this evening.

655
01:13:35.481 --> 01:13:36.349
We can come with you.

656
01:13:36.415 --> 01:13:37.717
Yeah.

657
01:13:37.784 --> 01:13:40.686
No, this is something
I'd rather do by myself.


658
01:13:42.621 --> 01:13:43.990
The nearest beach.

659
01:13:44.057 --> 01:13:46.492
Sunset's in a couple of hours,

660
01:13:46.559 --> 01:13:47.861
I think I'd better get going.

661
01:13:47.927 --> 01:13:52.498
I've experienced LA
traffic first hand.


662
01:13:52.565 --> 01:13:54.233
Alright, let's go.

663
01:14:02.408 --> 01:14:03.786
Tell you what, let
me take you both out


664
01:14:03.810 --> 01:14:05.411
for breakfast in the morning,

665
01:14:05.478 --> 01:14:07.280
then tomorrow night
I'll take you up


666
01:14:07.346 --> 01:14:09.015
on that dinner invitation.

667
01:14:09.082 --> 01:14:11.184
That sounds fine.

668
01:14:11.250 --> 01:14:14.821
Thanks again for
making this happen.


669
01:14:19.859 --> 01:14:21.995
Be safe, take care.

670
01:15:45.611 --> 01:15:50.083
There it is, Abigail,
just like you imagined.


671
01:15:54.120 --> 01:15:58.224
It's a beautiful sunset,
isn't it old friend?


672
01:16:00.026 --> 01:16:02.628
Joseph, what are
you doing here?


673
01:16:02.695 --> 01:16:03.930
Let me tell you a story

674
01:16:03.997 --> 01:16:06.832
as we watch the
light fade together.


675
01:16:06.900 --> 01:16:08.301
About a beloved wife,

676
01:16:08.367 --> 01:16:10.336
who asked for her husband
to join her in heaven


677
01:16:10.403 --> 01:16:15.041
after he finished his final
task of saving your daughter.


678
01:16:15.108 --> 01:16:16.575
Are you an angel?

679
01:16:16.642 --> 01:16:19.612
I was sent here to
accompany you on your journey,


680
01:16:19.678 --> 01:16:24.050
and asked to bring you home
when you were finished.


681
01:16:26.953 --> 01:16:29.255
It's time to go home Steven.

